COMPONENT NAME: IKM DB2 400 Slowly Changing Dimension
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Management of TYPE 2 Slowly Changing Dimensions on DB2/400 Tables. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled.
To use this Knowledge Module: When defining the Target Datastore, it is necessary to set the following parameters (from the "Slowly Changing Dimensions Behavior" list box, on the "Description" tab of each column concerned): - Surrogate Key: A single column identifying Records.This column must be created as an Identity column (with a GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY clause), and must be: - Mapped to 0 (zero) - Executed on Target - Natural Key: Column(s) representing the Natural Key of the Record. - Overwrite Column: List of updatable column(s) (i.e. those that can be updated after modification of the original data). - Insert Row: List of column(s) representing the Slowly Changing Attributes (i.e. those that require a Record insert after modification of the original data) - Current Record Flag: A single numeric column mapped to 0 or 1 and representing the Current Record Flag status of the Record. It is automatically updated by the Knowledge Module (1 : Current Record ; 0 : Past Records) - Start Timestamp: A single date (or timestamp) column indicating the beginning of a Record's availability. The value is the current date (or timestamp). - End Timestamp: A single date (or timestamp) column indicating the end of the Record's availability. The value is a default of "01 January 2039"
Restrictions: - Make sure to map ALL target table columns flagged as: "Surrogate Key", "Natural Key", "Current Record Flag", "Start Timestamp" and "End Timestamp". Notice that mappings set for the "Current Record Flag", "Start Timestamp" and "End Timestamp" columns are not used. - As this Knowledge Module is dedicated to Datawarehouse Projects (where data should not be removed), when using it with a journalized Source Datastore, it is not possible to synchronize deletions. Therefore, data should be manually filtered to exclude any source delete events (add a filter on JRN_FLAG = 'I'). - Deletes are committed regardless of the COMMIT option. - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. If the Table Primary Key is designated by the same column as the Surrogate Key, then: 1. On the "Diagram" tab of the Interface, uncheck the "Check Not Null" checkbox for the column representing the Primary Key. 2. On the "Control" tab of the Interface and in the "Constraint" panel, set the option value to NO for the Primary Key control. - To use this IKM, the temporary (C$, I$...) and target tables should be stored in AS400 collections (or AS400 journalized libraries), otherwise, an SQL7008 message will be signalled (refer to the IBM DB2/400 documentation for details concerning SQLCode 7008).
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected by flow control in a previous execution of this interface.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
This option generates an extra validation step. This step check that at least one column is marked as SCD_ADD and at least another one marked as SCD_UPD.

	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> IND_UPDATE ) <%for (int i=0; i < odiRef.getDataSetCount(); i++){%> <%=odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator")%> select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[DEST_WRI_DT](CAST('2039001' AS VARCHAR(10)), '00:00:00')", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> <% if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { %> JRN_FLAG IND_UPDATE <%} else {%> 'I' IND_UPDATE <%}%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom(i)%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJoin(i)%> <%=odiRef.getFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy(i)%> <%=odiRef.getHaving(i)%> <%}%>

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> IND_UPDATE ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> 'I' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> as E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> as T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "(SCD_NK)")%> ) and E.ODI_ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ODI_ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'
Create unique index on flow table

update <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S set IND_UPDATE = 'U' where exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= 1", "
		and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "((S.[COL_NAME] = T.[COL_NAME]) or ((S.[COL_NAME] is null) and (T.[COL_NAME] is null)))", "
		and	", "", "SCD_INS and !TRG")%> and ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "((S.[COL_NAME] <> T.[COL_NAME]) and ((S.[COL_NAME] is not null) or (T.[COL_NAME] is not null))) ", "
		 or	", "", "(SCD_UPD and !TRG)")%> ) )

update <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S set S.IND_UPDATE = 'N' where exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "S.[COL_NAME] = T.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	", "T.[COL_NAME] = 1", "
		and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("and	", "((S.[COL_NAME] = T.[COL_NAME]) or ((S.[COL_NAME] is null) and (T.[COL_NAME] is null)))", "
		and	", "", "(SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG")%> )

update <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T set ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "T.[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> ) = ( select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "X.[COL_NAME]",",
			","","(((SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[EXPRESSION]",",
			","","(((SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> X where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = X.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = 1", "
		and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'U' ) where exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = S.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = 1", "
		and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'U' )

update <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> T set ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_FLAG and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(SCD_END and REW)")%> ) = ( select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "0", ",
			", ",", "(SCD_FLAG and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "S.[COL_NAME]", ",
			", "", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = S.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> and S.IND_UPDATE = 'I' ) where exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = S.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "SCD_NK")%> and S.IND_UPDATE = 'I' and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = 1", "
		and	", "", "SCD_FLAG")%> )

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%if (!(odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", "", "", "((SCD_SK and TRG) and REW)").equals("0"))){out.print(odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", "", ",", "((SCD_SK and TRG) and REW)"));}%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",

	", ",", "(SCD_START and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",

	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", ",", "(((SCD_NK or SCD_INS or SCD_UPD) and TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "1", ",
	", ",", "(SCD_FLAG and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
